cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with using deep learning techniques to predict the time to collision between a robot and pedestrians using monocular video. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO) as it involves a robot being pushed by a user. The use of deep learning also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) could be relevant categories. Finally, the paper deals with the challenges of collision avoidance, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
